rget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://news.runletters.com/polls/31bcd6ba-0ef9-4bb3-86aa-4982a97c7f7f/response?pcid=bb4450d1-27eb-47fe-b414-0ee7b1df800c&ppid=9117a5c8-50fd-4644-b64d-0df828f3b1e3&sid=SUBSCRIBER_ID\"> 🌿 No music, but nature/environmental sounds are great! </a></li></ul></div></td></tr></table><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> It’s going to be a fun run today. Let’s get started ⤵️ </p></div><div style=\"background-color:transparent;border-color:#11296B;border-radius:20px;border-style:solid;border-width:3px;margin:20.0px 20.0px 20.0px 20.0px;padding:10.0px 10.0px 10.0px 10.0px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">Table of Contents</h2></div><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:42px;padding-right:32px;padding-top:12px;\"><ul style=\"color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:19px;list-style-type:disc;margin:0px 0px 0px 25px;padding:0;\"><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#watchlist-running-an-ultra-for-a-co\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">📹 Watchlist: Running an Ultra for a coffee</a></p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#social-spotlight-make-running-a-par\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">📲 Social Spotlight: Make Running a Party (with Ja …</a></p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#events-races-napa-valley-marathon\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">🗓 Events & Races: Napa Valley Marathon</a></p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#gear-gadgets-puma-deviate-pure-nitr\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">🎽 Gear & Gadgets: PUMA Deviate Pure Nitro</a></p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#wild-card-strength-for-runners\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">✨ Wild Card: Strength for Runners</a></p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"><a class=\"link\" href=\"#the-finish-line\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\" data-skip-tracking=\"true\">🏁 The Finish Line</a></p></li></ul></div></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"watchlist-running-an-ultra-for-a-co\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">📹 Watchlist: Running an Ultra for a coffee</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Will’s good friend James moves to Brighton, messing up their long-standing tradition: Will would run to a coffee shop, and they’d meet up for a cold brew and a cappuccino before going to work. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> So, Will decides he’ll run from London to Brighton. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> What follows is an <i>anything-but-gradual </i>buildup of mileage. The physio and doctor advise against it. And to make it even more “fun”, Will also needs to complete a challenge every day. </p></div><div class='p-4'><div class='mx-auto' id='e8153c0e-7642-49ce-bdaf-53799b45be9a' style='max-width: 520px;'><div class='relative' style='width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%'><iframe allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture' allowfullscreen class='absolute' frameborder='0' height='100%' src='https://youtube.com/embed/9aLWNixqiMU' style='top: 0; left: 0;' width='100%'></iframe></div></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> While the thumbnail and the concept are a bit gimmicky, you’ve got to respect the dedication Will has to completing his goal. Running 85k+ is never easy. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> I love how Will decides to break things up in 10k chunks. He’s definitely got some mental resilience, this guy. </p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"social-spotlight-make-running-a-par\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">📲 Social Spotlight: Make Running a Party (with Jay)</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Last week, I got a DM from a friend on Instagram. A friend who <i>does </i><b><i>not </i></b><i>run</i>. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> And the DM was about… running. It was this reel right here from Jay: </p></div><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:25px;padding-right:25px;padding-top:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DavWMOJtoQT/?utm_source=news.runletters.com&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=runletters-63\" style=\"padding:0; text-align:center; width:100%; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Instagram Post\" style=\"display: block; width: 100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c07eca39-ea02-41cd-8076-1b15a8b6ea42/instagram_screenshot_DavWMOJtoQT_1784281643_d1970b73.jpeg?t=1784281648\"/></a></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> At first, I thought it was going to be some comedy. A joke. Then I watched it, and I realized this DM was proof that Jay was achieving exactly what he had set out to do: turning non-runners into runners. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> I mean, the comments are <i>full </i>of them. People who’ve been wanting to run but who were lacking motivation. People who do run, but who need this extra push. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Jay’s got the voice for it. This is basically Nike Run Club on steroids. Coach Bennett turned into an MC. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> It’s not for me (I don’t really like listening to music while I run, haha), and I think it is best suited for treadmill runs, but… what an epic move. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Props to Jay. And just for these types of reels, <a class=\"link\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/jaycopley/?utm_source=news.runletters.com&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=runletters-63\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\">he’s worth a follow. </a></p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"events-races-napa-valley-marathon\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">🗓 Events & Races: Napa Valley Marathon</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> A fast course <i>and </i>vineyards? Sounds like a dream come true. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Twenty-three miles down the Silverado Trail, vineyards rolling past on both sides, and only four turns in the whole race (all of them in the final four miles). That&#39;s the Napa Valley Marathon for you. </p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;border-radius:20px;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/7348f202-a978-4ef2-983a-3aa84d031b29/image.png?t=1784292082\"/></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> It&#39;s a point-to-point course, starting up in Calistoga and finishing in Napa, with a gradual net downhill the whole way. People say it’s one of the best Boston Qualifying races in the country, and it shows: roughly 13% of finishers punch their BQ here. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Prefer the half? It starts a little further down the trail at Conn Creek. You get the same fast, scenic route, so it’s no less spectacular. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> The course’s speed isn’t the highlight here, though. It&#39;s the scenery. The reviews all talk about how incredible it is to watch the sun rise over the vineyards while fog settles into the valley below. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> This race isn’t around the corner, but that’s a good thing. First of all, because you can still sign up, and secondly, because it gives you enough time to train. </p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;border-radius:20px;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c25f30ac-47fe-4e15-b72d-b4b0906e9ba2/image.png?t=1784292113\"/></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> The next edition is on <b>Sunday, March 7, 2027</b> (marathon, half, or 5K!). </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> A perfect date because the weather is generally cool and kind. It’s also when the valley turns green before harvest season. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> It’s also a small race with a cap of just 3,000 marathoners. If you’ve read many editions of RunLetters, you know I’m a fan of races like this. Age-group winners get bottles of local wine (which is remarkably similar to a lot of races in Portugal, haha). After you finish, there&#39;s a party at Clif Family Winery, wine tasting included, and a massage a few minutes away at Health Spa Napa Valley if your legs need it. </p></div><div style=\"padding-bottom:14px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:14px;text-align:center;width:100%;word-break:break-word;\"><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\" href=\"http://napavalleymarathon.org/?utm_source=news.runletters.com&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=runletters-63\"><button style=\"background-color:#11296B;border-radius:10px;color:#FFFFFF;cursor:pointer;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;line-height:18px;padding:14px 14px;width:fit-content;\" type=\"button\"> Sign up here </button></a></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"gear-gadgets-puma-deviate-pure-nitr\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">🎽 Gear & Gadgets: PUMA Deviate Pure Nitro</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Last year, one of my fav shoes was the PUMA Deviate Nitro 3. I used it for my marathons and almost all my track workouts. So it’s no surprise that this new release from PUMA caught my eye. </p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:65%;border-radius:20px;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/0a7e5344-e8e3-4ae3-ba47-43475a2364b7/image.png?t=1784292873\"/></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> PUMA&#39;s Deviate Pure Nitro dropped June 4, and it&#39;s the first shoe in the family without a plate. No carbon, no rigid propulsion, just a 100% PEBA midsole (38mm heel / 30mm forefoot, 8mm drop). Which I think is ideal for most runners. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> I haven&#39;t run in it yet, so take this as an &quot;on my radar&quot; feature rather than a verdict. But early reviews are consistently good: comfortable, breathable upper, true to size, and a smooth, lively ride that testers describe as stable rather than mushy. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> It&#39;s about 30g lighter than the plated Deviate Nitro 4, and reviewers keep circling back to one word: value. At $150/€150/£129.99-150, it undercuts rivals like the Asics Superblast 3 while it’s got the same foam PUMA uses for its race-day shoes. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> People say that for the real fast intervals it’s less suited, but for most RunLetters readers I doubt this is the case. And many reviews <i>do</i> say the shoes are great for tempo runs, long steady miles, and easy runs (so great for half marathon training). </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Sizing note: the toe box runs slightly long, so check before you buy. Ideally, try them out in a store first. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"><b>TL:DR ⬇️</b></p></div><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:42px;padding-right:32px;padding-top:12px;\"><ul style=\"color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:19px;list-style-type:disc;margin:0px 0px 0px 25px;padding:0;\"><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"> Non-plated, 100% PEBA midsole </p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"> Best for: easy runs, tempo, long steady efforts </p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"> Not for: intervals or all-out speed work </p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"> Multipe colourways available </p></li><li style=\"margin:10px 0px 0px 0px;\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\"> $150 / €150 / £129.99-150 </p></li></ul></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"wild-card-strength-for-runners\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">✨ Wild Card: Strength for Runners</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Most runners completely skip strength and mobility work. They know it’s necessary, yet they don’t <i>do </i>it. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> I’m here to help with that. </p></div><div class='p-4'><div class='mx-auto' id='a7e58061-0682-4830-b575-f8422870a595' style='max-width: 520px;'><div class='relative' style='width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%'><iframe allow='accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture' allowfullscreen class='absolute' frameborder='0' height='100%' src='https://youtube.com/embed/CD8JL3hUhGk' style='top: 0; left: 0;' width='100%'></iframe></div></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> As part of my half marathon coaching program, I’ve been recording more workout videos. While in the program, you get access to two (live) sessions a week, I’m also actively building out a library full of workouts. Some of those go live on YouTube for <b>everyone</b>. </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> The account is still very new, but you can find it <a class=\"link\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@rl-runningworkouts?utm_source=news.runletters.com&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=runletters-63\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" style=\"-webkit-text-decoration:underline #11296b;color:#11296b;font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline #11296b;word-break:break-word;;\">here</a>. So far, I’ve uploaded most <b>with </b>and <b>without </b>music. What do you prefer? Please vote in the poll at the start of this newsletter. </p></div><div style=\"padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><img alt=\"\" style=\"margin:0 auto 0 auto;width:100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/8189dab1-0b1d-436d-8523-33505c204b0d/Runletters_divider.png?t=1746441141\"/></div></div><div id=\"the-finish-line\" style=\"padding-bottom:4px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:16px;\"><h2 style=\"color:#2A2A2A;font-family:'Helvetica',Arial,sans-serif;font-size:24px;font-weight:700;line-height:1.5;margin:0;text-align:left;\">🏁 The Finish Line</h2></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> That’s it for another edition of RunLetters! </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Here’s to a great weekend ahead ☀️ </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> Caroline </p></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"> P.S. Half marathon on the calendar? Or know someone who does? Check this out ⬇️ </p></div><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:25px;padding-right:25px;padding-top:20px;\"><div style=\"padding-bottom:20px;padding-left:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-top:20px;\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Daxw0cGoeVb/?utm_source=news.runletters.com&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=runletters-63\" style=\"padding:0; text-align:center; width:100%; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Instagram Post\" style=\"display: block; width: 100%;\" src=\"https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/c785b10e-f7f6-4ade-80e7-597ad852ed54/instagram_screenshot_Daxw0cGoeVb_1784293008_34ca565f.jpeg?t=1784293013\"/></a></div></div><style>\n  p span[style*=\"font-size\"] { line-height: 1.6; }\n</style><div style=\"padding-bottom:12px;padding-left:20px;padding-right:20px;padding-top:12px;\"><p style=\"color:#2D2D2D;color:var(--wt-text-on-background-color) !important;font-family:'Inter',-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Roboto,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;\"></p></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>, \"images\":  }"